author = "E. Anastassakis and E. Burstein",
abstract = "In the presence of an applied external force the symmetry of the vibrational modes of a 
crystal changes in a way which depends on the nature of the force. The resulting ‘morphic effects’ 
on the absorption and scattering of electromagnetic radiation may allow one to observe an otherwise 
inactive mode, and thereby reveal information about its character. We present here a general method 
for describing the dynamical behavior of any vibrational mode in any non-magnetic crystal structure 
